               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380917-name-281" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-281" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-281" type="surname" value="HUGHES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-281" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT HUGHES</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner was my foreman for about sixteen on the—it was his business to take care of these articles—from informa<lb></lb>tion, I sent to the officer—I knew the prisoner lodged in Gilbert-street—I saw this property there—I believe the whole is mine, but part of it I can speak to more particularly—that property had no business at his lodgings.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you ever see these things on your premises? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I have seen these curtains and drapery, and this velvet—I cannot say that I saw all, but I believe I did—part of it I speak Positively to, and I believe the whole is mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18380917-name-282" type="witnessName">
